This project predicts whether a customer is likely to churn using historical customer data.
The goal is to help the Customer Value Management (CVM) team identify at-risk customers early.

Business Problem
Customer churn directly impacts revenue.
Retaining existing customers is cheaper than acquiring new ones.
This model helps prioritize retention campaigns.

Dataset
- Customer demographics
- Contract details
- Monthly charges
- Tenure
- Target variable: Churn (Yes/No)

Approach
1. Data cleaning & preprocessing
2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
3. Feature encoding
4. Train/Test split
5. Logistic Regression model
6. Model evaluation
7. Business interpretation

Model & Metrics
- Model: Logistic Regression
- Metrics used:
  - Accuracy
  - Precision
  - Recall
  - F1-score
